---
const benefits = [
  {
    title: 'One workflow across every agent',
    body: 'Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Gemini, Cline, Aider, Continue, Windsurf, OpenCode — they all read the same CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md / GEMINI.md and the same context docs. Switch tools, keep your project context.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Project-type aware',
    body: 'Web, Backend-API, Mobile-Desktop, Other. The scaffold flow adapts — Web gets framework picker + shadcn opt-in; backends skip the UI bits; everything still gets the same workflow brain.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Strategy docs, not just code patterns',
    body: 'thesis.md gives the agent the why. project-overview.md gives the what. coding-standards.md gives the how. Decisions you make once stop getting re-asked every session.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Real feature lifecycle, real branches',
    body: 'The /feature loop is git-aware: it cuts branches, writes per-feature specs, updates current-feature.md, merges back, and writes history. Not a thin chat wrapper.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Predictable, opt-in execution',
    body: 'Slash commands and agents never auto-fire. /cleanup runs when you ask. code-scanner reviews on demand. Mutations need permission. The agent acts like a teammate, not a poltergeist.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Updates compound',
    body: 'Improve a skill in a real project, copy it back into the npm package, bump the version. Your future self and your collaborators inherit the improvement on the next install.',
  },
];
---

<section class="relative">
  <div class="container-page py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-[var(--color-hairline)]">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <span class="eyebrow">Why bother</span>
      <h2
        class="mt-3 text-[var(--color-ink)] text-balance font-semibold"
        style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3.25rem); line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.025em;"
      >
        What you get.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-[var(--color-ink-muted)] text-pretty" style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.55; letter-spacing: -0.005em;">
        Six things the scaffold does for you on every project so you don't have to set them up by
        hand each time.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-px bg-[var(--color-hairline)] border border-[var(--color-hairline)] rounded-[12px] overflow-hidden md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {benefits.map((b) => (
        <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-1)] p-6 md:p-7 hover:bg-[var(--color-surface-2)] transition-colors">
          <h3 class="text-[var(--color-ink)] font-semibold text-[16px] tracking-tight">{b.title}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[14px] text-[var(--color-ink-muted)] leading-[1.55]">{b.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
